    "content": "**\"Experience\"** as main translation, with **\"empirical experience\"** as the disambiguation form used when 体验 and 经验 appear in close proximity.\n\nReasoning: The author uses 经验 most frequently as an adjective — \"经验的总结,\" \"经验的预测,\" \"经验性的\" — which translate naturally as \"empirical summary,\" \"empirical prediction,\" \"empirical.\" When 经验 appears as a noun in running text, plain \"experience\" reads cleanly and the accumulated/reflected-upon sense is usually clear from context (\"经验结构\" = \"experiential structure,\" \"经验与模式\" = \"experience and patterns\"). Prepending \"empirical\" every time would be heavy in exactly the passages where it is least needed.\n\nThe real collision risk is only where 体验 and 经验 appear within a few sentences of each other. In those passages, \"empirical experience\" disambiguates. Everywhere else, \"experience\" is sufficient and the TN handles the rest."
  }
